Description:
    The `piktur new` command creates a new Rails application with a default
    directory structure and configuration at the path you specify.

    The template:
      - adds core gems to Gemfile
      - creates local repo
      - creates remote repo [bitbucket]
        - adds remote
        - commit/push
        - checkout 'develop'
      - creates Heroku remote [production, staging]
        - adds domain alias [production, staging]
        - enables addons [newrelic]
        - sets env
        - sets maintenance mode
      - CircleCI integration

Example:
    cd piktur
    bin/piktur new blog